.TH scale_what_if_capacitance  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBscale_what_if_capacitance\fR \-  Scales the intrinsic cell capacitance value to determine how much additional capacitance can be added in a region to reduce dynamic IR drop
.SH Syntax  \fBscale_what_if_capacitance\fR   [-help]   -reset | {{-global | -region <x1 y1 x2 y2> | -cell <cell_name> | -instance <inst_name>| -file <filename>}  [-instrinsic_cap <value>]  [-loading_cap <value>]   [-grid_cap <value>]  [-add]  [-layer <name>]  [-net <net_name>]  } 
.P Scales the intrinsic cell capacitance value to determine how much additional capacitance can be added in a region to reduce dynamic IR drop. 
.SH Parameters    "\fB-add \fR" Specifies to add capacitance (farads) on the power-grid on a specific layer and region. The parameter works in conjunction with the existing parameters, such as -intrinsic_cap, -grid_cap, and -loading_cap. When this parameter is specified, the value provided with the -intrinsic_cap, -grid_cap, and -loading_cap parameters will be treated as absolute value instead of a scale factor value, which is the default behavior.  "\fB-cell <cell_name>\fR" Specifies to scale the capacitance value for the specified cell.   "\fB-file <filename>\fR" Specifies a file containing the list of instances and cells that use the same scaling factor. The format of the file is:  CELL <cellname>   INSTANCE <instancename>  "\fB-global | -region <x1 y1 x2 y2>\fR" You must specify either -global or -region <x1 y1 x2 y2>. The -global option scales the specified capacitances for the entire design.  The -region <x1 y1 x2 y2> scales the specified capacitances in the region. The default unit of <x1 y1 x2 y2> is in database units  "\fB-grid_cap <value>\fR" Scales power-grid capacitance of the design to the specified scale factor. The default scale value is 1.  Note: The -grid_cap parameter can be specified either with the -global or the -region parameter. This parameter is not supported with the -cell and -instance parameters.   "\fB-help\fR" Outputs a brief description that includes the type and default information for each scale_what_if_capacitance parameter.  For a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use the man command: man scale_what_if_capacitance.  "\fB-instance <inst_name>\fR" Specifies to scale the capacitance value for the specified instance.   "\fB-intrinsic_cap <value>\fR" Scales instance internal gate capacitances to the specified scale factor. The default scale value is 1.  "\fB-layer<layername |>all\fR" Specifies the LEF layer on which capacitance scaling is performed. Multiple commands can be issued to scale capacitance on multiple layers. You can specify the all argument to scale all the layers.  "\fB-loading_cap <value>\fR" Scales loading capacitance of the instance to the specified scale factor. The default scale value is 1.  "\fB-net <net_name>\fR" Specifies to scale the capacitance value for the specified net.   "\fB-reset\fR" Resets all the previous scale_what_if_capacitance command settings. 
.SH Examples
.RS  "*" 2  Cell-based capacitance scaling - The following command scales intrinsic capacitance on all instances of the cell cellA by 1e-10 (<intrinsic_cap> * 1e-10):  scale_what_if_capacitance -cell cellA  -intrinsic_cap 1e-10  "*" 2  Pin-based capacitance scaling - The following command scales intrinsic and loading capacitance on all instances of the cell cellA connected to the pin vdd  by 1e-10 (<intrinsic_cap> * 1e-10 and <loading_cap> *1e-10):  scale_what_if_capacitance -cell cellA -net vdd -intrinsic_cap 1e-10  -add -loading_cap 1e-10  "*" 2  Region-based capacitance scaling - The following command scales capacitance in the specified region by 1e-10 (<intrinsic_cap> * 1e-10, <loading_cap> *1e-10, and <grid_cap> * 1e-10):  scale_what_if_capacitance  -region {896.877  937.661  1276.9365  1615.358} -intrinsic_cap 1e-10   -loading_cap 1e-10  -grid_cap 1e-10  "*" 2 The following command scales grid capacitance in the specified layer by 1e-10:  scale_what_if_capacitance -net VDD -region { 0 0 100 100 } -layer M2 -grid_cap 1e-10
.RE 
.SH Related Information
.RS  "*" 2 create_current_region   "*" 2 scale_what_if_resistance  "*" 2 scale_what_if_current  "*" 2 "What-If Rail Analysis" in the Voltus IC Power Integrity Solution User Guide
.RE
